S . AFRICAN APRIL TRACTOR SALES DIP 15 PERCENT YR / YR . South African tractor sales were 15 . 2 percent down on a year ago in April at 368 units , although in the year to date sales were 6 . 7 percent ahead of last year , the Agricultural Machinery Association said on Monday . The association said the disappointing sales could reflect poor weather in February and March , causing uncertainty about summer crops , and worries about lower international maize prices . - - Johannesburg newsroom + 27 11 482 1003 
